metadata.description: Denver II Developmental Screening Questions - KiddyGuard V2 Format

questions.questionText: Does your baby look at your face?
Does your baby seem happy to see you when you walk up to her?
Does your baby smile when you talk to or smile at her (a "social smile")?
Does your baby calm down when spoken to or picked up?
Does your baby recognize his parent or primary caregiver?
Does your baby stop crying when held by a familiar, soothing person?
Does your baby open his hands briefly?
Does your baby watch you as you move from side to side?
Does your baby look at a toy for several seconds?
Does your baby follow a moving object with her eyes past the midline of her face?
Does your baby hold her hands unfisted about half of the time?
Does your baby retain a rattle if it is placed in his hand?
Does your baby make sounds other than crying (like gurgling or cooing)?
Does your baby react to loud sounds?
Does your baby turn his head toward sounds?
Does your baby startle when he hears a loud noise?
Does your baby make throaty noises?
Does your baby seem to listen when you talk to her?
Does your baby hold his head up when on his tummy, even for a moment?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your baby lifting their head while lying on their tummy.

questions.questionText: Does your baby move both arms and both legs?
Does your baby lift his chest up when lying on his stomach?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your baby pushing their chest up with their arms while on their tummy.

questions.questionText: Does your baby kick his legs when lying on his back?
Does your baby turn his head from side to side when lying on his stomach?
Does your baby have movements that seem smooth (not jerky)?
Does your baby smile on his own to get your attention?
Does your baby chuckle (not a full laugh) when you try to make her laugh?
Does your baby look at you, move, or make sounds to get or keep your attention?
Does your baby stop crying at the sound of a parent's voice?
Does your baby enjoy looking at other people?
Does your baby cry in different ways to show hunger, pain, or being tired?
Does your baby look at his hands with interest?
Does your baby hold a toy when you put it in her hand?
Does your baby use her arm to swing at toys?
Does your baby bring her hands to her mouth?
Does your baby follow a moving object in a circle when lying on his back?
Does your baby reach for a toy with both hands?
Does your baby make cooing sounds like "oooo" or "aahh"?
Does your baby make sounds back when you talk to him?
Does your baby turn her head towards the sound of your voice?
Does your baby gurgle or make other happy sounds?
Does your baby seem to recognize your voice?
Does your baby quiet down or smile when you talk?
Does your baby hold his head steady without support when you are holding him?
Does your baby push up onto his elbows or forearms when on his tummy?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your baby on their tummy, showing if they push up onto their elbows.

questions.questionText: Does your baby roll from his tummy to his back?
Does your baby push down with his legs when his feet are on a hard surface?
Does your baby sit with his trunk supported (for example, propped with pillows)?
Does your baby have no head lag when you pull him to a sitting position?
Does your baby know familiar people from strangers?
Does your baby like to look at himself in a mirror?
Does your baby laugh?
Does your baby smile responsively at you?
Does your baby like to play with you?
Does your baby feed herself a cracker or cookie?
Does your baby reach to grab a toy he wants?
Does your baby close her hand around a rattle you put in it?
Does your baby bring things to his mouth to explore them?
Does your baby transfer a toy from one hand to the other?
Does your baby use a "raking" grasp (using all fingers) to pull small objects closer?
Does your baby shake a rattle?
Does your baby take turns making sounds with you?
Does your baby blow "raspberries" (sticking tongue out and blowing)?
Does your baby make squealing noises?
Does your baby coo and babble?
Does your baby respond to her own name?
Does your baby make different sounds to show feelings like joy or unhappiness?
Does your baby roll from his tummy to his back, and his back to his tummy?
Does your baby push up with straight arms when on his tummy?
Does your baby sit up with little or no support?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your baby sitting on the floor without leaning on anything or anyone for at least 5 seconds.

questions.questionText: When standing with support, does your baby bounce up and down?
Does your baby lean on her hands for support when sitting?
Does your baby bear weight on his legs when held in a standing position?
Does your baby show shyness, clinginess, or fear around strangers?
Does your baby show several facial expressions, like happy, sad, angry, and surprised?
Does your baby react when you leave (looks for you, reaches for you, or cries)?
Does your baby smile or laugh when you play peek-a-boo?
Does your baby wave "bye-bye"?
Does your baby play gesture games like "pat-a-cake"?
Does your baby move things from one hand to her other hand easily?
Does your baby use fingers to "rake" food towards himself?
Does your baby bang two things together (like blocks or spoons)?
Does your baby pick up small things, like pieces of cereal, with his thumb and index finger (pincer grasp)?
Does your baby voluntarily let go of objects?
Does your baby poke at things with her index finger?
Does your baby make a lot of different sounds like "mamamama" and "bababababa"?
Does your baby lift his arms up to be picked up?
Does your baby look when you call her name?
Does your baby copy the sounds and gestures you make?
Does your baby understand "no"? (pauses briefly when you say it)
Does your baby say "dada" or "mama" even if not for a specific person?
Does your baby get to a sitting position by herself?
Does your baby sit without support?
Does your baby pull up to a standing position while holding on to furniture?
Does your baby crawl on hands and knees?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your baby crawling on hands and knees across the floor.

questions.questionText: Does your baby stand while holding on to something for 10 seconds or more?
Does your baby move from lying down to sitting up without help?
Does your child play games with you, like pat-a-cake or peek-a-boo?
Does your child wave "bye-bye"?
Does your child show you things by bringing them to you or holding them up?
Does your child drink from a cup without a lid, as you hold it?
Does your child feed herself with her fingers?
Does your child offer a toy to you when you ask for it, even if he doesn't let go?
Does your child pick up a crumb or Cheerio with the tips of her thumb and a finger?
Does your child put a small toy in a cup?
Does your child bang two blocks together?
Does your child help turn the pages of a book?
Does your child scribble on paper after you show him how?
Does your child poke at or try to get a small object that is inside a clear bottle?
Does your child say "mama" or "dada" for the correct parent?
Does your child say at least one word other than "mama" or "dada"?
Does your child follow a simple one-step command with a gesture?
When you ask, "Where is the ball?" does your baby look at the ball?
Does your child try to imitate the words you say?
Does your child use gestures like shaking his head for "no"?
Does your child pull up to a standing position and walk by holding onto furniture ("cruising")?
Does your child stand alone for a few moments?
Does your child take a few steps without holding on?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your child taking several steps without holding onto anything.

questions.questionText: Does your child lower herself to a sitting position with control?
Does your child get into a sitting position without help?
Does your child sit well without support?
Does your child imitate you doing household chores, like sweeping or dusting?
Does your child show affection to family members, pets, or stuffed animals?
Does your child help you dress him by pushing his arm through a sleeve or lifting his foot?
Does your child play with a doll or stuffed animal by hugging, feeding, or rocking it?
Does your child point to show you something interesting?
Does your child try to get your attention by making sounds or movements?
Does your child stack two blocks?
Does your child scribble on paper when you give her a crayon?
Does your child put a small object in a container?
Does your child turn the pages of a book one at a time?
Does your child use a spoon to feed herself?
Does your child point with her index finger?
Does your child say at least 3 words other than "mama" or "dada"?
Does your child follow a simple command without gestures, like "Give me the ball"?
Does your child point to a picture of a familiar object when you name it?
Does your child try to say words you say?
Does your child use gestures along with sounds to communicate?
Does your child understand simple questions like "Where is your nose?"
Does your child walk alone?
Does your child walk up stairs with help?
Does your child run?
Does your child throw a ball forward?
Does your child kick a ball forward?
Does your child climb on furniture?
Does your child help with simple household tasks?
Does your child show pride in accomplishments?
Does your child play alongside other children?
Does your child show you things he has made or done?
Does your child imitate adult activities?
Does your child show independence by doing things on his own?
Does your child stack 3 blocks?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your child successfully stacking at least three small blocks on top of each other.

questions.questionText: Does your child turn the pages of a book one at a time?
Does your child use a spoon to feed herself?
Does your child scribble with a crayon?
Does your child put small objects into a container?
Does your child point with her index finger?
Does your child say at least 10 words?
Does your child follow a two-step command like "Get the ball and bring it to me"?
Does your child point to body parts when you name them?
Does your child use two-word phrases like "more milk" or "bye-bye daddy"?
Does your child ask for things by name?
Does your child understand simple questions?
Does your child walk up stairs holding the railing?
Does your child run without falling?
Does your child kick a ball forward?
Does your child throw a ball overhand?
Does your child jump in place?
Does your child walk backwards?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your child taking several steps backward without holding onto anything.

Does your child show concern when another child is hurt?
Does your child help with simple tasks?
Does your child show pride in accomplishments?
Does your child imitate adult activities?

Does your child stack 6 blocks?

Does your child use pronouns like "I" and "me"?
Does your child walk up stairs alternating feet?
questions.videoInstruction: Record your child walking up stairs, showing if they place one foot per step.
